# ==============================================================================
# File: .gitignore
# Brief: Git ignore rules for generated Craftworld files.
#
# Details:
#   Git uses this file to decide which files should not be committed. Build
#   directories, executables, libraries, object files, local editor settings, and
#   operating-system junk files are generated or machine-specific, so they should
#   stay out of version control.
#
#   For a beginner: this file prevents temporary files from cluttering the
#   project history.
